        <num>CC 3039</num>
        <heading>3039.  Suretyship requires no formal acceptance</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 3039.  Suretyship requires no formal acceptance
Suretyship is established upon receipt by the creditor of the writing evidencing the surety's obligation.  The creditor's acceptance is presumed and no notice of acceptance is required.</p>
        </content>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=110081</p>
